item.title: [ENTESB-1154] Create dummy patch jars to test patch
item.description:
Hi,

WE need to create some sort of test jars to test the patching capabilities of 6.1. The following areas should be covered:

1. Fabric container
2. Non-fabric container

I don't think this needs to be fancy. I'm thinking of some jars that when installed/started print a message to the log which we can grep. Hopefully we can automate part of the test. Probably best to do some checks in Fabric itself, MQ, Camel.
item.summary: Create dummy patch jars to test patch

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Susan Javurek - BTW, you select the versino you want to patch from the "Manage" page, then in the textbox you can either leave it blank to use the next version number in the sequence, or tell the patching mechanism what version to use next. I haven't gotten a chance to get everything set up to test this yet, but that could be the reason for the error, as you're patching 1.0 and you've specified 1.0 should be the new version to patch.

Susan Javurek fixed the hawtio error -> http://fusesource.com/forge/git/hawtio.git/?p=hawtio.git;a=commit;h=b47f8eee30fa0cafd6f9caaf7bdfca7a2b7bf2c7

now I'm getting the same error as the command-line patch tool, likely an issue with the patching service.

Susan Javurek The problem you're seeing with the hawtio patch is due to a rename in the artifacts that happened recently. If you rebuild the test patches against a more recent assembly, you'll notice that the M bit in the middle of the artifact name is gone.

Also, I'm attaching a new variant of the build.gradle script that will also include the WAR files into the patch (e.g. for hawtio), so if you're rebuilding the test patches, make sure to grab the last copy of the script here as well.

Thanks Gert. I'll pick up the new files shortly.

Do you have any thoughts on the stack trace from the command line patching for fabric. The error is #2 from the comment on Monday 17th.

I'm working on a fix to the patching service.
See https://github.com/fabric8io/fabric8/pull/933
The 370 build has Guillaume's fix in it. So it is ready to verify.
I'll give it a whirl this afternoon in hawtio for fabric patching...

Fired up build 370 and tried to apply a patch via hawtio. I still get:
